This paper involves the use of machine learning techniques for decision-making in autonomous driving, which falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The use of imitation learning and reinforcement learning methods suggests that the paper could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.RO (Robotics). The focus on learning sequential decision-making policies and control policies suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of simulation environments and evaluation metrics suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
